3a:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["When you want to copy an instance, just call ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"typia.misc.clone()"}]," function. It would perform deep copy including nested objects, so you can get a new instance with same values. Also, if you want type safe deep copy function, you can use ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"typia.misc.isClone()"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"typia.misc.assertClone()"}]," or ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"typia.misc.validateClone()"}]," functions instead."]}]
